node.statement: PART 3 (q-BPS states and q-Witten index): The q-deformed Hamiltonian H_q admits BPS states (ker H_q) whose count is given by a q-deformed Witten index W_q(r) = Tr[(-1)^F exp(2pi i r R_q)]. For j odd and q > 0 real, D^BPS_q(j, Â±1/6) is a q-deformation of 3^j computable from the representation ring of U_q(su(2)).
